657. Robot Return to Origin
https://leetcode.com/problems/robot-return-to-origin/description/?envType=daily-question&envId=2026-04-05
Que in my words: a robot is at origin in 2D plane, given string where string[i] tells where the robots moves, up,down,left and right, we need to tell if after all those moves is it possible for robot to be at origin again.
Approach: 1) kept a counter, incremented it when encountered "UP" and "Right" and decremented when encountered "Down" and "Left". At the end checked if the collected sum is 0 or not.
Issue with this approach: hit this test case :
        
"UDDUURLRLLRRUDUDLLRLURLRLRLUUDLULRULRLDDDUDDDDLRRDDRDRLRLURRLLRUDURULULRDRDLURLUDRRLRLDDLUUULUDUUUUL"
here we had :
L: 27

R: 25

D: 22

U: 26

the total sum will be 0 but we can see that we need to check if user is compensating its move in both X and Y direction, by the above logic the total sum is 0 but user has moved left/right and up/down more with this robot can never make to origin.
Fix: keep track of the movement of robot in both the direction, robot should walk in opposite direction equally so that the movement gets compensated and returns back to origin.


Code:
class Solution {
public:
//TC:O(n)
//SC:O(1)
    bool judgeCircle(string moves) {
        int n = moves.size();
        int totalCntX = 0;
        int totalCntY = 0;
        for(int i = 0 ; i < n ; i++){
            if(moves[i] == 'U'){
                totalCntX += 1;
            }
            else if(moves[i] == 'D'){
                totalCntX -= 1;
            }
            else if(moves[i] == 'R'){
                totalCntY += 2;
            }
            else{
                totalCntY -= 2;
            }
        }
        
        return totalCntX == 0 && totalCntY == 0;
    }
};
